[DQR.IFRS.0126.9595] The statement 06 - Rapport över kassaflöden includes an inconsistent calculation. The value of the concept ifrs-full:CashFlowsFromUsedInInvestingActivities of -4,252,100,000 should be equal to the sum of its child components defined in the calculation linkbase. The sum of these child components is -4,253,200,000. The values of the addends is determined by adding the values of the child concepts with a decimal value of -5. All values in the financial statements should use the same decimal value. The values reported in the financial statement in the current reporting period of 2021-01-01 to 2021-12-31 should be complete if the financial statement is to be mathematically accurate and complete. The components of ifrs-full:CashFlowsFromUsedInInvestingActivities that should add to -4,252,100,000 are comprised of the following:
- InvestmentsInInvestmentProperties 254,600,000 - PurchaseOfInvestmentProperty 3,994,200,000 - PurchaseOfPropertyPlantAndEquipmentClassifiedAsInvestingActivities 4,400,000
The addends are calculated based on the calculation linkbase defined for 06 - Rapport över kassaflöden. If addends are missing then the calculation tree should be amended. The rule will not add dimension components as the financial statement does not include a table. If dimensions are used on the statement then add a table to ensure that the dimensions are defined correctly.
